article.headline: Arkansas St. 90, New Orleans 79
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Isaac Wells scored 22 points and snared 13 rebounds Thursday night as Arkansas State beat New Orleans 90-79 in a Sun Belt Conference matchup. Wells made 50 percent of his field-goal attempts and was 9-of-10 at the free-throw line. Arkansas State (13-14, 8-7 SBC) led 38-31 at the half. Adrian Banks scored 19 for the Indians and Ryan Wedel had 18, while Shawn Morgan added 12 points. UNO (12-14, 8-7) was led by Shaun Reynolds with 26 points, while James Parlow scored 23 and Bo McCalebb made 17. McCalebb also grabbed 10 rebounds.
